					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466378#post-1438917</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466378/scp-1424#post-1438917</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 05 May 2012 16:02:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>VAElynx</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>914331</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>SCP-1424 has a bodily temperature that ranges between -23 to -18&#160;°C and extrudes trace amounts of ammonia through its tongue and paws continually, causing a significant health risk to personnel exposed in an unventilated space for a long enough period of time</p> </blockquote> <p>This is just bad. Firstly , a trace amount is an amount that can be detected, but is so small it's hard or meaningless to quantify. Exposure to trace amounts of ammonia wouldn't be harmful to anyone.</p> <p>Secondly , &quot;long enough period of time&quot; is a very zen method of specifying safe exposure times that has nothing at all to do in a document of this sort. It gives absolutely no information for J. Random Researcher that needs to work with the puppy.</p> <p>Other than that, I kinda like this one.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
